This is the README for Video::Subtitle::SRT version 0.04.

Video::Subtitle::SRT is a "module" for the Perl computer programming language,
a library of computer code to install on a computer.  This document contains
four sections:

1. About - what the module does

2. Documentation - how to learn more about the module

3. Installation - how to install this module on a computer

4. Help - what to do if you get stuck

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. ABOUT

Video::Subtitle::SRT - manipulate SRT subtitle files

Video::Subtitle::SRT is a callback based parser to parse SubRip
subtitle files (.SRT). See "bin/adjust-srt" how to use this module to
create subtitle delay adjusting tools.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

2. DOCUMENTATION

You can read the documentation for the module online at the following websites:

    * http://search.cpan.org/perldoc?Video::Subtitle::SRT
    * http://metacpan.org/release/Video-Subtitle-SRT

(These links go to the latest version of the module.)

After installing the module, you can read the documentation on your computer
using

    perldoc Video::Subtitle::SRT

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

3. INSTALLATION

This module requires Perl version 5.6.1 or later.

To install the module from CPAN, use

    cpan Video::Subtitle::SRT

If you have the App::cpanminus installer, you may prefer

    cpanm Video::Subtitle::SRT

To install the module from the source file, Video-Subtitle-SRT-0.04.tar.gz,
follow this sequence of commands:

    tar xfz Video-Subtitle-SRT-0.04.tar.gz
    cd Video-Subtitle-SRT-0.04
    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make install

If you want to test the module before installing it, use "make test" after
"make" and before "make install".

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

4. HELP

To get help with the module, you can email the author, Ben Bullock, at
<bkb@cpan.org>. If you think there is a problem in the module, you can report a
bug at 

<https://github.com/benkasminbullock/Video-Subtitle-SRT/issues>,

or if you want to alter the source code of Video::Subtitle::SRT, try the public
repository on github at 

<https://github.com/benkasminbullock/Video-Subtitle-SRT>. 

